article.headline: UT-Chattanooga 77, Austin Peay 67
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. (AP) -- Casey Long scored 19 points and grabbed 7 rebounds, leading Chattanooga to a 77-67 win over Austin Peay on Saturday night. After 14 lead changes and nine ties, Chattanooga (11-9, 2-3 Southern Conference) took the lead on a Khalil Hartwell basket with 7:09 left to play, putting the Mocs up 63-61. Zac Schlader tied a career high with 27 points for Austin Peay (11-8, 6-4 Ohio Valley). He was 11-of-11 from the free throw line and completed eight-of-10 field goals. Drake Reed added another 10 points for the Governors. Jerice Crouch and Charles Anderson both added 15 points for the Mocs. Steve Cherry netted 11 points and had 9 rebounds. Chattanooga forced 21 turnovers and had 14 steals. The Mocs' win marks their fourth-straight over the Austin Peay.
